<p>Our paper is featured on the Front Cover of Nanophotonics!</p>

<ul>
  <li>Cover story: https://doi.org/10.1002/nap2.70126</li>
  <li>Full paper: https://doi.org/10.1002/nap2.70079</li>
</ul>

<figure class="figure">
  <a class="figure-image">
    
      <!-- It's a standard image (jpg, png, webp) -->
      <img src="/images/news/2026/05/Nanophotonics/nanophotonics-cover.jpg" style="width: 400px;" alt="" loading="lazy" />
    
  </a>
  
  
</figure>

<p>In this work, we present a hybrid optoelectronic imaging system for ultra-low-power edge detection. An l=2 encoded spiral metalens optically computes second-order edge information while a compressive sensing CMOS image sensor captures a reduced set of measurements, enabling high-speed, energy-efficient edge-aware imaging without bulky digital postprocessing. Our simulation results show a peak signal-to-noise ratio of 23.87 dB at a 25% compression rate, demonstrating that the metalens can preprocess the scene and the compressive sensing sensor can recover high-fidelity edge images using only one-quarter of the full sensor data.</p>

<p>This paper is a collaboration with Prof. Hyunkeun Lee and the CICS lab at Korea University Sejong Campus: https://cics.korea.ac.kr</p>

<p><a id="korean-version"></a></p>

